# Claude Code Agent Instructions

## Before Starting Any Task

**Required reading order:**
1. Read "project" memory file for current state and data models
2. Read "architecture" memory file for structural decisions  
3. Read "conventions" memory file for code patterns
4. Check existing files in target directory before creating new ones
5. If modifying existing files, read them completely first

**Task interpretation:**
- Acceptance criteria are requirements, not suggestions
- If database schema is needed, create Supabase migration first
- If auth is needed for a feature, implement the auth flow first
- Build incrementally — get basic version working before adding complexity

## Working Rules

**Before committing code:**
```bash
npm run build  # Must pass without errors
npx tsc --noEmit  # Must pass type checking
npm run lint  # Must pass ESLint
```

**File creation rules:**
- Every new app/ page needs proper TypeScript types
- API routes go in app/api/ with route.ts naming
- Shared components go in src/components/
- Database types go in src/types/database.ts
- Create loading.tsx and error.tsx for pages that need them

**Modification rules:**
- Before modifying lib/ files, check all their imports across the codebase
- Never overwrite scaffold files unless fixing specific bugs
- When adding API routes, implement proper auth checks first
- When creating database operations, test RLS policies work

**Import rules:**
- Use @/ path mapping for all internal imports
- Import Supabase clients from lib/supabase/server or lib/supabase/client
- Never import from @supabase/supabase-js directly
- Use Next.js built-ins: `import { NextRequest, NextResponse } from 'next/server'`

## Commit Conventions

**Format:** `type(scope): description`

**Valid types:**
- feat: new feature
- fix: bug fix  
- db: database schema changes
- auth: authentication changes
- api: API route changes
- ui: component/styling changes
- config: configuration changes

**Scope examples:** auth, entries, mood, analytics, api, db

**One commit:**
- Single feature implementation
- Related file changes (component + API route)
- Bug fix with test

**Multiple commits:**
- Database schema (separate commit)
- API implementation (separate commit)  
- UI implementation (separate commit)
- Large features spanning multiple pages

**Commit body:**
- List the files changed
- Explain any architectural decisions
- Note any breaking changes

## PR Rules

**Before opening PR:**
- All checks pass: `npm run build && npx tsc --noEmit && npm run lint`
- Test the feature works end-to-end
- Verify auth restrictions work correctly
- Check responsive design on mobile

**PR description format:**
```
## What
[Brief description of changes]

## Why  
[Why this change was needed]

## Testing
[How to test the changes]

## Files
- Added: [new files]
- Modified: [changed files]
- Removed: [deleted files]
```

## What This Agent Must Never Do

**Security violations:**
- Never expose API keys in client-side code
- Never skip auth checks in protected API routes
- Never commit .env files or secrets
- Never create database operations without RLS policies

**Architecture violations:**
- Never modify scaffold files in root/ unless fixing bugs
- Never use Pages Router patterns (use App Router)
- Never import Supabase clients incorrectly
- Never put server-only code in client components

**Code quality violations:**
- Never commit code that doesn't pass TypeScript checks
- Never use `any` types without justification
- Never create API routes without proper error handling
- Never skip input validation on API endpoints

**Project violations:**
- Never implement features without checking user limits (5 entries/day, 3 mood logs/day)
- Never give free users access to AI features
- Never create public endpoints for user data
- Never bypass the established Supabase client patterns